Short Description: Capturing the main content of the scene.
Dense Description: Detailing the scene’s content, which notably includes scene transitions and camera movements that are integrated with the visual content, such as camera follows some subject.
Background: Describing the environment in which the subject is situated.
Style: Characterizing the style of the video, such as documentary, cinematic, realistic, or sci-fi.
Shot Type: Identifying the type of video shot that highlights or emphasizes specific visual content, such as aerial shot, close-up shot, medium shot, or long shot.
Lighting: Describing the lighting conditions of the video.
Atmosphere: Conveying the atmosphere of the video, such as cozy, tense, or mysterious.

nodes.title: Tips:
widgets_values:
TIPS:

- hide noodles by pressing the 
  dedicated ComfyUI button in the 
  bottom right "👁️"

- Go to SETTINGS, search for:
  "Display animated previews when 
  sampling"
  Turn it ON to watch the video 
  build directly in the sampler 
  node.

- Fast Lora may works best when 
  combined with other Loras, 
  allowing you to reduce the 
  number of steps.

- Wave Speed can significantly 
  reduce inference time but may 
  introduce artifacts.

- Achieving good results requires 
  testing different settings. 
  Default configurations may not 
  always work, especially when 
  using LORAs, so experiment to 
  find settings that fits best.

- If you're experiencing poor 
  results or glitches, you can 
  also try to switch to different 
  sampler/scheduler, such as 
  LCM, DDPM, DDMPP_2M, Euler or 
  the new "Gradient_estimation"
  (Samplers/schedulers need to be 
  set for each stage and mode; 
  they are not settings found in 
  the console)

- Set the pause node as you prefer. 
  By default, the node wont pause the 
  workflow, meaning the upscaling is 
  done automatically. 
  Simply select: 
  "Always Pause" 
  to force pause the workflow before 
  upscaling.

- For pure I2V try LeapFusion V1, 
  wich may works better in a wider 
  range of cases. try it yourself.
  I got bets results using it with 
  LCM and fast lora
